/** @page PAGE_GeometryPartOverview GeometryPart Overview

@tableofcontents

A @b DgnGeometryPart is used to persist geometry that is in common between multiple elements.
This has the potential benefit of greatly reducing file size and improving ease of maintenance.

@see DgnGeometryPart
@see DgnGeometryPartId
@see DgnGeometryParts
@see GeometryBuilder

<hr>
<!-- ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------- -->
@section PAGE_GeometryPartOverview1 Insert a DgnGeometryPart

The following code demonstrates how to create and insert a DgnGeometryPart.
The basic steps are:

- Create desired geometric primitives.  A convenient local origin is defined.
- Use a GeometryBuilder to append geometric primitives into a single <i>geometry stream</i>
- Create a %DgnGeometryPart with a given name (DgnCode)
- Associate the geometry stream with the geometry part
- Insert the geometry part into the %DgnDb

@note A geometry stream must be entirely 2D or entirely 3D

__PUBLISH_INSERT_FILE__ ToyTile_InsertGeometryPart.sampleCode

